=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Pulse_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 4.0839
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1273
  pitch_clarity: 48.7600
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -15.4451
  resonance_freq: 193.7988

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Pulse Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Pulse.html
// Tags: Pulse, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// modulate frequency
{ Pulse.ar(XLine.kr(40, 4000, 6), 0.1, 0.2) }.play;

// modulate pulse width
{ Pulse.ar(200, SinOsc.kr(0.2).range(0.01, 0.99), 0.2) }.play;

// two band limited square waves thru a resonant low pass filter
{ RLPF.ar(Pulse.ar([100, 250], 0.5, 0.1), XLine.kr(8000, 400, 5), 0.05) }.play;
